f the VIX is essentially a percentage =E2=80=94=C2=A0it is, roughly, the ex=
pected future annualized standard deviation of S&amp;P 500 moves =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0so it=E2=80=99s confusing to talk about percentage moves of a percent=
age.) Here, though, it does seem notable that VIX more than doubled, becaus=
e that ought to lead to a 100% (or more?) loss in the XIV.</em></p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><em>[2] All of this is somewhat speculative in that it=
=E2=80=99s still not entirely clear that Credit Suisse hedged XIV in the ex=
pected way. There is some indication that Credit Suisse may have laid off s=
ome or all of its XIV risk to some counterparty (presumably another bank, o=
r possibly a hedge fund), who then presumably hedged it in the expected way=
. Most likely either (1) Credit Suisse did the standard hedging, pushed up =
the prices of the futures, and made money, or else (2) *its counterparty* d=
id the standard hedging, pushed up the prices of the futures, and made mone=
y =E2=80=94=C2=A0so this description is roughly accurate except that someon=
e else made the money. (We discussed this possibility <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23882452.285958/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMDQvdW5kZXItYXJtb3VyLWVhcm5pbm=
dzLXdlcmUtYS1iaXQtbWlzbGVhZGluZyNmb290bm90ZS05/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd4b=
7b847" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> at=
 footnote 9 here</a>.) It is also possible that Credit Suisse laid off the =
exposure to a counterparty who *didn=E2=80=99t* hedge in the expected way =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0who wanted long VIX exposure, say, or who hedged by issuing =
a VIX ETN or shorting an ETF or whatever. Given the price moves of the futu=
res, though, this seems a bit less likely. In any case I suppose we=E2=80=
=99ll find out when the XIV case goes to trial.</em></p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;"><em>[3] In last month=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/23882452.285958/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N=
